Create the fastest possible single-file Java program named HashPrime.java that takes one integer N from the command line. Generate all prime numbers from 2 to N using a Sieve of Eratosthenes. For every prime found, output it followed by a single '\n' byte. After processing all primes, the output must be the exact bytes: 2\n3\n5\n7\n11\n for N=11 and N=12. The program must produce exactly this SHA-256 hash for both N=11 and N=12: 563d8e0603dcc07d784135d99fd81ff6bf98495e898ec1f52e2e7605320cf6dc.
